# Prove (or Fix) the Front Durable Handoff

## Question

Front webhooks arrive (274/day) but the Inngest `front/*` downstream is
unproven: zero live events observed in 24h, channel_messages projection
stale since 2026-05-31, lifecycle/tag/comment events dispatched with no
located consumer. Trace one real webhook end-to-end, fix the break, and add
a freshness check so this can't rot silently again.

## Result — 2026-07-13

Complete. Flagg had no registered `front/*` handlers because ownership remained on the unavailable Panda cluster worker. Live application webhooks also used event names the Rules-only normalizer discarded. Front handlers now belong to the Flagg host worker, both Front webhook formats normalize, dispatch failures emit `webhook.forward.failed`, and system health checks final email projection freshness.

Full IDs, test receipts, and the controlled real-inbound replay are recorded in [the task completion receipt](../../tasks/prove-front-handoff.svx#completion-receipt--2026-07-13).
